      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism is a profoundly double-edged sword, capable of both unifying and dividing. When channeled constructively, it fosters a shared sense of identity and purpose necessary for a cohesive society to function. However, when it devolves into chauvinism or xenophobia, it becomes an inherently dangerous ideology that justifies aggression and oppression. Therefore, its danger lies not in its existence, but in how it is wielded by its adherents.",
